{"name":"Curse Item","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You spend 10 minutes imbuing a curse upon an item. Choose one spell you can cast with the curse trait and one item of 2 Bulk or less you can handle during this activity. The spell must be able to affect at least one creature, and you cast this spell at the end of this activity. If the spell takes longer than 10 minutes to cast, increase the time required for this activity to match the casting time. The spell triggers immediately when a creature other than you attempts to hold, manipulate, activate, or otherwise use the item, and targets only that creature. The item gains the cursed trait, with a level equal to yours.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"curse-item","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333718403,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"17Xuz0KkDakqrZ5Z"}
{"name":"Curse Expansion","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your connection with curses has grown, and you can use your cursebringer abilities more often. You can cast each occult innate spell granted by cursebringer archetype feats one additional time per day. You can do this for spells of all levels granted, other than your two highest spell levels from non-cantrip cursebringer spells. If you have @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-cursebringer.YwbCvknR3oJQUwxb]{Heightened Curses}, you can Cast the chosen Spell a second time each day, though one of the two times you cast it, it’s heightened two levels lower than your highest level of non-cantrip cursebringer spells, as long as the spell can be cast at that spell level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"curse-expansion","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333724507,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"7wJCoMKOzYkKr9Tb"}
{"name":"Curse Resilience","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You attempt a save against a curse effect. If you have previously @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recalled Knowledge} about this curse, then this is a free action; otherwise, it’s a reaction.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Attempt to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge} about the triggering curse.</p>\n<p>If you have previously @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recalled Knowledge} about this curse, you can use the result of that check, instead. You gain the following benefits in addition to the usual outcomes.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> You gain a +2 circumstance bonus on the triggering save.</p>\n<p><strong>Success </strong>You gain a +1 circumstance bonus on the triggering save.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"curse-resilience","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Cursebringer Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333689980,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"84SgWlRQYy9zZsd9"}
{"name":"Cursebringer Dedication","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You are a focal point for misfortune. Choose Curse Lore or Occultism. You become trained in that skill, or become an expert if you were already trained.</p>\n<p>Choose two cantrips with the curse trait, including class-specific cantrips such as the witch’s @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.f45JpY7Ph2cAJGW2]{Evil Eye}. For you, these are occult cantrips. You gain access to the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} activity and can cast these spells as occult innate spells.</p>\n<p>You’re trained in occult spell attack rolls and spell DCs.</p>\n<p>If you have a hand free, you can usually replace material components with somatic components, so you don’t need to use a spell component pouch. You may choose Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma as your key spellcasting ability for your cursebringer spells.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You can’t select another dedication feat until you’ve gained two other feats from the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-magic-journals.6DPJqrJJBdYR5hbz.JournalEntryPage.9TwW4cBTGxy9fTwE]{Cursebringer} archetype.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.proficiencies.traditions.occult.rank","value":1}],"slug":"cursebringer-dedication","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["archetype","dedication"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"trained in Curse Lore or Occultism"},{"value":"Intelligence 14, Wisdom14, or Charisma 14"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333542160,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"9I3W4ahjdua0NBso"}
{"name":"Expert Cursebringer Spellcasting","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You learn more powerful curses. You learn a 4th-level spell. At 12th level, you learn a 5th-level spell, and at 14th level, you learn a 6th-level spell. Each of these spells must have the curse trait, or it can be @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.OyFCwQuw8XRazsNr]{Remove Curse}. You Cast these Spells as occult innate spells.</p>\n<p>You become an expert with spell attack rolls and spell DCs for occult spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.proficiencies.traditions.occult.rank","value":2}],"slug":"expert-cursebringer-spellcasting","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333781804,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"9XbEF9zJkCIeoZeH"}
{"name":"Master Cursebringer Spellcasting","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You master the most powerful spells connected to negative energy. You learn a 7th-level spell. At 18th level, you learn an 8th-level spell, and at 20th level, you learn a 9th-level spell. Each of these spells must have the curse trait, or it can be @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.OyFCwQuw8XRazsNr]{Remove Curse}. You cast these spells as occult innate spells.</p>\n<p>You become a master with spell attack rolls and spell DCs for occult spells.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"system.proficiencies.traditions.occult.rank","value":2}],"slug":"master-cursebringer-spellcasting","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":16},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Expert Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333802865,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"OVELfRqAUxJsQzXI"}
{"name":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your connection to curses develops into full-fledged spellcasting. This spellcasting comes to you naturally but you must use your learnedness about curses to control it. Choose a 1st-level spell. You can Cast this Spell as a occult innate spell once per day. At 6th level, you gain a 2nd-level spell, and at 8th level, you gain a 3rd-level spell. Each of these spells must have the curse trait.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"basic-cursebringer-spellcasting","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Cursebringer Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333550823,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"P20wCrshV9fXSjZx"}
{"name":"Heightened Curses","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You can infuse your curse spells with more power.</p>\n<p>Choose one of your spells granted by cursebringer archetype feats; this spell can’t be from your highest level of non-cantrip cursebringer spells. The spell you choose is heightened to the highest level of cursebringer spell you can cast, not including cantrips. You can’t later change the spell that is heightened by this feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You can select this feat more than once. Each time you select it, you choose a different spell.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"heightened-curses","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":null,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333739445,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"YwbCvknR3oJQUwxb"}
{"name":"Countercurse","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>A creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Casts a Spell} with the curse trait</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You have an innate non-cantrip cursebringer spell you haven’t cast yet today.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You attempt to redirect the triggering curse. When a foe casts a spell with the curse trait and you can see its manifestations, you can use your own innate magic to disrupt it. You lose an innate, non-cantrip spell as if you had @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast the Spell}. You then attempt to counteract the triggering spell with your spell. On a critical success, the triggering creature becomes targeted by the curse spell, and takes a -2 circumstance penalty to their defense against it.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"countercurse","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333733421,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"jBl5w9RHScn6Fslr"}
{"name":"Reactive Cursing","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You are the target of a spell or attack.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You lash out with a curse at your attacker. You cast any of your 1st-level cursebringer spells that normally take two actions or fewer to cast. This takes effect before the triggering spell or attack, and if the attacker is affected by your spell, it can make different decisions based on the effects (for instance, if your curse imposes a penalty to the triggering effect, the attacker can choose a different target). The attacking creature must be in range of your chosen spell, and if your spell requires targets, the attacking creature must be a valid target.</p>\n<p>Your spell affects only the attacking creature, even if it would normally affect more targets or an area.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"reactive-cursing","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"day"}},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333793021,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qCP8yl655zkuYQTU"}
{"name":"Persistent Curse","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your curse effects are persistent. If your next action is to cast a spell with the curse trait and it all targets avoid its effects, you do not lose the spell. You must use the same number of actions to recast the same spell on your following turn; if you can’t, or choose not to, you waste that number of actions with no effect. After this second casting, you lose the spell whether it affected any targets or not. @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-cursebringer.zJ5WaCUHsS2KvBPq]{Persistent Curse} works only with spells that require targets and doesn’t do anything if you cast a targeted spell but didn’t select any targets.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic - Magic Specializations"},"rules":[],"slug":"persistent-curse","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":18},"traits":{"value":["archetype","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Basic Cursebringer Spellcasting"}]},"location":null,"frequency":{"max":1,"per":"day"}},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686115227694,"modifiedTime":1686333816544,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"zJ5WaCUHsS2KvBPq"}
